---
<section data-test="problem-section" style="padding:4rem 1.5rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);background:var(--color-surface);">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">
    <h2 style="font-size:0.75rem;font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--color-text-muted);margin-bottom:1.5rem;">The Problem</h2>
    <h3 style="font-size:clamp(1.4rem,3vw,2rem);font-weight:300;line-height:1.3;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:var(--color-text);max-width:680px;margin-bottom:2rem;">
      Every existing approach fails the same way: the spec and the code drift apart.
    </h3>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
      <div>
        <h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-text);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Spec drift is inevitable</h4>
        <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.65;">By the time validation happens, it's far removed from the original intent. Every intermediate step drifts independently.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-text);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">TDD and BDD don't stick</h4>
        <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.65;">They transform a few pages of spec into a book of pedantic instructions. Expensive, tedious, and abandoned the moment a deadline appears.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-text);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">AI makes it faster, not better</h4>
        <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.65;">Throwing AI at TDD just automates the tedium without fixing the underlying problem. The drift is still there — it just happens faster.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
